cat << EOF
Clipboardmanager for GNOME and other WMs. You can see this as a GNOME
counterpart to KDE's Klipper. But it only depends on GTK+ 2 and NOT on GNOME
libs, so you can also use it with any other window manager that supports
tray icons.
EOF
